Popular singer 2Baba has reiterated the need for Nigerians to be actively involved in electing their leaders. Addressing his fans which included celebrities in an Instagram live video, the globally celebrated singer urge them to do away with the notion that their votes doesn’t count. “If you participate, it’s what you participate in that you get and if you don’t; you will get result of your non-participation. “Right now no matter how you think your vote doesn’t count, if you turn it to a culture, it’ll eventually count,” he said.   I won’t do another plastic surgery even with…     Tinubu only brand that can beat Atiku – Shettima     Buhari signs 2022 amended Appropriation Act   Stressing on the need for active participation in election, 2Baba warned that citizens who refuse to have automatically lost their right to speak whether to complain or anything of the sort. “Las las Naija don cast. Nothing fit happen again unless everybody participate. And if you don’t participate, there is no need for you to talk. “You don’t have a right to open your mouth and talk if you don’t participate. You no get right to open mouth to criticise anybody, to do anything, if you don’t participate. That is the way I see it now,” the singer added.